<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-22] Several matrix exceptions are checked exceptions, but should be unchecked</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-22</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;IndexException and CardinalityException should be unchecked exceptions by analogy to ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Having them be checked causes lots of try/catches in code that doesn&apos;t have a chance of fixing the problem.  It should be understood that these can happen in any matrix manipulation code just like IllegalArgumentException, ArithmeticException or ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException can happen in any numerical codes. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
